Scotia Mortgage Corp is issuing a 100 mlnCanadian dlr eurobond due April 9, 1992 paying 8-3/4 pct andpriced at 100-3/4 pct, lead manager Wood Gundy Ltd said.    The non-callable bond is available in denominations of1,000 and 10,000 Canadian dlrs and will be listed inLuxembourg. It is guaranteed by the Bank of Nova Scotia. Theselling concession is 1-1/4 pct, while management pays 1/4 pctand underwriting pays 3/8 pct.    The payment date is April 8 and there will be a long firstcoupon period. Reuter&#3;